{ "answer": ["Colchicine"], "clues": ["The Ebers Papyrus, one of the oldest surviving medical texts from ancient Egypt from 1550 BC, describes uses of the autumn crocus to treat pain and swelling. This medication was later derived from this plant.","In Greek mythology, the autumn crocus was said to have sprung from the blood of the chained Titan Prometheus. Medea, a powerful sorceress, used the autumn crocus as one of her poisons as this substance binds to tubulin to suppress cell division and has a narrow therapeutic window.","A versatile anti-inflammatory medication, this is used in Familial Mediterranean Fever, pericarditis, and most commonly gouty arthritis"] },
